review_blob: Wheat and barley aroma. It has an amber and carmel color. it has a lot of hops and a wheat flavor.
Its aroma is average. It smells like plain generic beer. It is an amber-brown in color. It tastes like generic beer. It has a lot of hops. A lot of flavor.
It is a ruby red color. It has a sweet raspberry aroma. The flavor of this beer is fruity. Lots of raspberry, blackberry, and strawberry flavor. Very delicious!
Dead Guy Ale has a sweet and honey- like aroma. It is an orange carmel color.It has a sour, light, and tart flavor. Full flavored beer.
Refreshing. The lime adds a nice taste. An improvement over bud light. Light and fresh taste. average taste and aroma.
Average aroma and flavor. Light in color. LIght, great summer beer. Great presentation. Can sometimes come off as a little skunky.
Good beer for the price. Cheaper than most IPAs. Smooth taste. Deep reddish gold in color. Has a high level of hops.

It has an amber dark orange appearance. Its aroma is fruity, strawberry, and sweet. I didnt expect to enjoy this as much as I did. Its overall flavor and taste is fizzy, cream soda, sweet, strawberry, and slightly carbonated.
A clear light golden brown in color and appearance. has a smooth finish. Offers a fuller taste and mouthfeel then Budweisser. Citrus and grain taste and aroma.
Mad Hatter has a licorice aroma and taste. Dark copper in color. Tangy and hoppy taste. Also some pine in the taste.
Amber and light orange in color. Has a mix of citrus, pine, and floral hops to it. Light body.
Fruity cherry flavor. Much better then I expected. Delicious! It is a pinkish cherry red color. It has a fresh, sweet, and crisp flavor.
Has a very sweet and smooth taste. Not too sweet. One of my favorite ciders. Clear golden flavor.
Great citrus flavors (orange, lemon, lime). Nice wheat flavors. Light and refreshing. Great for a summer day.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)

A great IPA! Hoppy and refreshing. Has a citrus and and grapefruit element.
generic taste, cool bottle, chicago brewed, and nice to drink in nice weather
